|Cultural information=The Persian word "rahbar" is a broad term for leader used in various contexts, after the Islamic Revolution of 1979 the term has come to refer to the office of the Ayatollah. The phrase "rahbar-i inqilab" [leader of the revolution] refers to Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini. The official office of Ayatollah Sayyid Ali Khamenei, the current leader of the Islamic Republic is: daftar-i maqam-i mu'azam-i rahbari, lit. the office of the exalted figure of leadership. As such, the English frame "state leadership" approximates the Persian
